                  "file_data": null,
                  "function_call": null,
                  "function_response": null,
                  "inline_data": null,
                  "text": "To see the brake pressure and apply the parking brake in a Bombardier Challenger 605, follow the instructions below based on the aircraft's landing gear and hydraulic systems documentation:\n\n### **1. Where to see Brake Pressure**\nYou can monitor the real-time pressure for both inboard and outboard brakes on the **HYDRAULIC Synoptic Page** of the EICAS (Engine Indication and Crew Alerting System).\n*   **Location:** This information is found on the EICAS display, specifically under the **HYDRAULIC Synoptic Page**.\n*   **Reference:** **Figure 15−10−8** (HYDRAULIC Synoptic Page - Inboard and Outboard Brake Pressure) on **page 15** of the **CL605-LANDING_GEAR** document.\n*   **Note:** If the brake system pressure falls below **1,015 psi**, the EICAS will display `INBD BRAKE PRESS` or `OUTBD BRAKE PRESS` caution messages.\n\n### **2. How to \"Turn on\" (Apply) the Parking Brake**\nThe parking brake is controlled by a dedicated handle typically located in the cockpit center pedestal area.\n*   **Control Handle Location:** Refer to **Figure 15−10−9** (Parking Brake) and **Figure 15−10−10** (PARKING BRAKE Handle) on **page 15 and 16** of the **CL605-LANDING_GEAR** document.\n*   **Procedure to Apply:**\n    1.  Fully **depress both brake pedals** (on either the pilot’s or copilot’s side).\n    2.  **Pull the PARKING BRAKE handle** up.\n    3.  **Rotate the handle 90°** to the locked position.\n*   **Confirmation:** Once applied, the EICAS will display a green `PARKING BRAKE ON` advisory message (**page 15**).\n\n### **3. Operational Requirements**\n*   For both the inboard and outboard brakes to hold pressure, **Hydraulic Systems 2 and 3** must be pressurized. \n*   If hydraulic systems are turned off, only the inboard brakes will hold for a prolonged period via the accumulator (**page 15**).\n\n**Reference Summary:**\n*   **Brake Pressure View:** Figure 15-10-8 (CL605-LANDING_GEAR, Page 15).\n*   **Parking Brake Handle:** Figure 15-10-9 / 15-10-10 (CL605-LANDING_GEAR, Page 15-16).\n*   **Application Steps:** CL605-LANDING_GEAR, Page 15.",
